ENDPOINT PROTECTION PLAN - Ahmnest SecureTech Solution
================================================================================
Effective Date: [Date]
Version: 1.0
================================================================================

1. OVERVIEW
================================================================================
This document outlines the endpoint protection strategy for all company devices
including workstations, servers, and mobile devices.

2. PROTECTION TYPES
================================================================================
| Protection Type | Solution | Coverage |
|-----------------|----------|----------|
| Antivirus/Anti-Malware | CrowdStrike Falcon | All endpoints |
| Endpoint Detection (EDR) | CrowdStrike Falcon | All endpoints |
| Application Whitelisting | Windows Defender Application Control | Servers |
| Vulnerability Scanning | Qualys | All endpoints |
| Patch Management | Microsoft SCCM | All endpoints |
| Encryption | BitLocker/FileVault | Laptops/Desktops |

3. PATCH MANAGEMENT
================================================================================
| System Type | Patch Schedule | Emergency Patches | Owner |
|-------------|----------------|-------------------|-------|
| Windows Servers | Monthly (2nd Tuesday) | Within 48 hours | IT |
| Linux Servers | Monthly (1st Friday) | Within 48 hours | IT |
| Workstations | Automatic | ASAP | IT |
| Network Devices | Quarterly | Within 24 hours | IT |
| Cloud Services | Automatic | N/A | Cloud Provider |

4. MOBILE DEVICE MANAGEMENT
================================================================================
| Policy | Requirement | Enforcement |
|--------|-------------|-------------|
| Screen Lock | 4-digit PIN | MDM Policy |
| Encryption | Required | MDM Policy |
| Remote Wipe | Enabled | MDM Policy |
| Jailbreak Detection | Block access | MDM Policy |
| App Store Only | Required | MDM Policy |

5. REMEDIATION PROCEDURES
================================================================================
| Finding | Action | Timeline |
|---------|--------|----------|
| Malware Detected | Isolate device, EDR response | Immediate |
| Patch Missing | Deploy patch | 48 hours |
| Unauthorized Software | Uninstall | 24 hours |
| Policy Violation | User notification | 24 hours |
| Critical Vulnerability | Emergency patch | 8 hours |

================================================================================
